KPA Air Force Command Gives One More Warning to U.S. Imperialists 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, June 12 (KCNA) -- The U.S. imperialist warmongers committed one more grave military provocation by illegally infiltrating a strategic reconnaissance plane into the sky above the DPRK's economic waters on June 12. In this regard the Air Force Command of the Korean People's Army issued the following report on Monday:
 At around 12:05 on June 12, an overseas-based strategic reconnaissance plane of the U.S. imperialist aggression forces infiltrated into the sky above the waters of the DPRK east of Chongjin and Hwadae and made a shuttle flight there for hours to spy on its strategic targets.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Such ceaseless illegal infiltration and aerial espionage are arousing a bitter indignation from the officers and men of the KPA Air Force. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is an indigenous disposition of our revolutionary armed forces to mercilessly punish the aggressors. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The KPA Air Force warns again that the U.S. imperialist warmongers will be buried in the East Sea of Korea if they continue running amuck without discretion despite our warnings.

Kim Jong Il's Greetings to Putin 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, June 12 (KCNA) -- Kim Jong Il, chairman of the DPRK National Defence Commission, Monday sent a message of greetings to Russian President Vladimir Vladimirovich Putin on the occasion of the national day of Russia.
 The message said: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 I extend warm congratulations to you and the government and people of your country on the national day of the Russian Federation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 I express conviction that the long traditional friendly and cooperative relations between the two countries would continue to develop in depth in different fields in conformity with the common aspiration and desire of the two peoples in the future, too. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 I wholeheartedly wish you greater success in your responsible work to achieve the socio-political stability and economic development and build a powerful country and the friendly people of your country fresh prosperity and well-being.

Songun Idea Praised in Foreign Countries 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, June 12 (KCNA) -- The 42nd anniversary of leader Kim Jong Il's start of work at the Central Committee of the Workers' Party of Korea was commemorated in Bangladesh and Democratic Congo on June 2 and 3.
 A reporter and speakers at a joint seminar on the Songun idea and the anti-imperialist struggle held in Barisal, Bangladesh said that the Songun idea based on the Juche idea founded by President Kim Il Sung, great leader and father of socialist Korea, is the most correct guiding idea for the accomplishment of the cause of independence against imperialism. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The present situation requires the popular masses to embody the Songun idea in the struggle for the building of a new society, they said, calling upon the adherents of the Juche idea to deeply study the validity and vitality of the Songun idea which were verified in practices and conduct energetic activities for applying it to the reality. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 At a reading session on the brief biography of Kim Jong Il held in Kinshasa, the chairman of the National Committee of the Genuine Lumumbist Patriotic Party of Democratic Congo said that he, possessed of transparent political philosophy, has led the revolution and construction to victory with his unique political mode for more than 40 years since he started his work at the Central Committee of the WPK.

Special Internet Homepage on DPRK Opens 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, June 12 (KCNA) -- The Communist Party of Great Britain (Marxist-Leninist) opened a special Internet homepage on June 2 on the occasion of the 42nd anniversary of leader Kim Jong Il's start of work at the Central Committee of the Workers' Party of Korea.
 Seen on the homepage is a portrait of Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In its preface the homepage said that Kim Jong Il considered it his lifelong mission to accomplish the revolutionary cause of Juche started by President Kim Il Sung and has performed immortal exploits for the Party, the revolution, the country and the people, noting that he is a great successor to the revolutionary cause of Juche, supreme commander of the revolutionary armed forces and leader of the people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Jong Il has ushered in a new era of eternal prosperity for Kim Il Sung's Korea through his tireless revolutionary activities for the last more than four decades, it stressed. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It also edited articles explaining his propositions on the immortal Juche idea and the revolutionary cause of Juche and photos showing the national flag and emblem of the DPRK.

National Day of Russian Federation Observed 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, June 12 (KCNA) -- The Korean people extend warm congratulations and friendly greetings to the Russian people on the national day of the Russian Federation, says Rodong Sinmun in a signed article Monday.
 Noting that energetic work is in progress in Russia to build a powerful state, the article goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Russia is developing friendly and cooperative relations with other countries, maintaining an anti-war and peace-loving stand in its external affairs. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Its government is striving to develop in depth good neighborly relations of friendship and cooperation with the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK-Russia relations are now growing in scope and developing comprehensively in many fields, political, economic, scientific and technological and cultural. The bilateral friendly ties are plumbing new depth with each passing day. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The development of the friendly and cooperative relations between the two countries is giving impetus to the building of a great prosperous powerful nation by the Korean people and the building of a powerful state by the Russian people and helping toward peace and security of Asia and the rest of the world. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The efforts of the Russian government and people to defend the country's strategic interests and security and achieve social development will bear substantial fruits.

Belgian Woman Lawyer Gives Impressions of Revisit to Korea 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, June 12 (KCNA) -- Belgian woman lawyer Marie-Louise Moerens on a visit to the DPRK was interviewed by KCNA at Pyongyang Koryo Hotel on June 10.
 Asked about impressions of her revisit to Korea after the lapse of many decades, she said: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This is my second visit to Korea. I paid the first visit in March 1952 in the thick of the Korean War. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 At that time I was a member of an investigation group of the International Association of Democratic Lawyers for delving into the brutalities of U.S. troops in Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In those days Korea was utterly reduced to debris in the war provoked by the United States. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Bombs exploded without letup on the ground. But we appreciated a performance by artistes with Pyongyang citizens at the underground theatre in the city and could see a general plan for the rehabilitation and reconstruction of Pyongyang City. This plan convinced us that the Korean people were waging a winning war and the U.S. would be defeated by them. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The current visit has left deep impressions upon me. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 I fancied I was having a dream, looking over Pyongyang which has changed beyond recognition today with grand monumental edifices, modern high-rise buildings and rows of apartment houses that sprang up on the ruins to which everything had been reduced in U.S. bombings. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 All these are a brilliant fruition of the devoted efforts of the Korean people under the wise leadership of President Kim Il Sung and leader Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Yesterday and today of Korea caught me up in a flood of thought. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 While staying here, I could witness the indomitable fight of the Korean people to defend and glorify their idea and system, not yielding to the maneuvers of the imperialist allied forces to crush the country, and directly feel the breathing of the heroic people advancing vigorously for the building of a great prosperous powerful socialist nation, closely united around the great leader. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Korean people will surely win in their struggle for justice, peace and socialism.

Youth and Students Urged to Foil Anti-Reunification Conservatives' Moves in S. Korea 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, June 12 (KCNA) -- The South Headquarters of the National Alliance of Youth and Students for the Country's Reunification, in an article titled "The 6th anniversary of the publication of the June 15 joint declaration and our tasks" issued on June 8, called on the youth and students to take the lead in the struggle to foil the "Grand National Party" and other anti-reunification conservative forces' moves against the DPRK.
 Now that the GNP is working hard to block the movement of the Koreans for reunification through an offensive against the June 15 joint declaration and provoke a new war in collusion with the U.S., the youth and students have an urgent task to foil its moves on their own initiative. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Urging the Koreans in the south and the north and overseas to declare before the world their unshakable determination to achieve national cooperation against the U.S. at the upcoming grand festival for national reunification, the article underlined the need for the forces for the nation and democracy to form a grand alliance against conservatives with rare awareness and determination and transparent anti-Americanism. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is the only way of achieving reunification for the nation to realize reconciliation and unity between the south and the north, the article notes, calling for using the grand festival for national reunification to mark the 6th anniversary of the June 15 joint declaration as an occasion of bringing about a signal turn in the development of the movement for reunification.

Seminar on Revival of Japanese Militarism Held in Germany
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, June 12 (KCNA) -- A seminar on the revival of militarism in Japan and peace in Northeast Asia was held in Berlin on May 30.
 Present at the seminar were Han Jong Ro, representative of the Korean Women's Society for Peace in Germany, university professors from south Korea and Germany and Korean Germans. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Speakers at the seminar blasted Japan for becoming all the more undisguised in its moves to revive militarism as evidenced by its distortion of history textbooks, its claim to Tok Islet, the chief executive's visit to the Yasukuni Shrine and its revision of "the pacifist constitution".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Accusing Japan of making a bid for permanent membership of the UN Security Council, far from honestly reflecting on its past crimes and apologizing for them, they called upon the Koreans at home and abroad and the world progressives to unite close and stage anti-Japanese actions in various forms and ways.

S. Koreans' Protest Goes On in U.S.
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, June 12 (KCNA) -- A group of demonstrators from south Korea keeps staging anti-U.S. actions in Washington day after day, according to Internet Homepage of Minjok Thongsin in the U.S.
 On June 6 the group held in front of the White House a meeting protesting the U.S. expansion of its war bases on the Korean Peninsula and its war moves there. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Speakers at the meeting vehemently denounced the U.S. expansion of war bases and its war moves in south Korea, holding photos showing south Korean military and police forces forcibly removing Taechu primary school on May 4. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Korean Americans and activists of an anti-war peace movement organization in the U.S. also made speeches. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 On June 7 the group marched from the Capitol Hill to the White House in protest against the conclusion of the "Free Trade Agreement".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The march was participated in by Father Mun Kyu Hyon of the south Korean Catholic Priests' Council for Justice, Kang Ki Gap, lawmaker from the Democratic Workers' Party, O Jong Ryol, permanent chairman of the National Alliance for Democracy and Reunification and other members of the group, Korean Americans and members of the anti-war peace movement organization in the U.S.

Functional Haemostatic Bandage Made in DPRK
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, June 12 (KCNA) -- Teachers and researchers of Han Tok Su Pyongyang University of Light Industry of the DPRK have succeeded in making functional haemostatic bandage.
 The bandage is called "water-soluble haemostatic bandage". It dissolves well in water like pulp. When it is applied to wound, it absorbs moisture in blood and lymph. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Also it activates hematopexin by anion in blood to stop bleeding quickly. And it, treated by antibacterial drug, prevents contamination and heals a wound quickly. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The bandage applied to a wound is absorbed partly into human body and the rest can be washed away after it is healed up. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The research team has also made an absorbable bandage for operation, which is absorbed within the body. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The bandage does not need the second-stage operation and prevents adhesion of bowels. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The newly developed bandages are highly appreciated in medical service.

Brilliant life of Kim Chol Ju
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, June 12 (KCNA) -- The Korean people, with deep emotion, are looking back upon the revolutionary life of Kim Chol Ju, an indomitable revolutionary fighter, who devoted himself to the struggle for the liberation of the country.
 He was born in Mangyongdae-dong, Mangyongdae District, Pyongyang (then Nam-ri, Kophyong sub-county, Taedong County, South Phyongan Province) on June 12, Juche5 (1916) as the second son of Kim Hyong Jik, an outstanding leader of the anti-Japanese national liberation movement in Korea, and Kang Pan Sok, an outstanding leader of the Korean women's movement. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He, who left Mangyongdae in his early years along with his parents, spent his childhood full of vicissitudes at Kangdong of Korea, Linjiang, Badaogou, Fusong and Antu of China, experiencing the distress and misfortune of a ruined nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Under the meticulous guidance and warm care of President Kim Il Sung, his elder brother, he acquired the truth of the revolution and grew up to be a true revolutionary who was possessed of indomitable fighting spirit, firm will, lofty personality and virtues. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He became a core member of the Saenal Children�fs Union, the first children�fs revolutionary organization in Korea organized by the President and took an active part in art performances for educating and enlightening popular masses and in the publication and distribution of the newspaper �gSaenal�h. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He joined the Young Communist League in 1929. He solidly built up and expanded the YCL organizations in different areas and trained young people through the revolutionary struggle against the Japanese imperialists. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 True to the teachings of the President, he made a distinguished service to carrying the line of united front into practice under the banner of the anti-Japanese joint front and to strengthening the mass foundation of the anti-Japanese armed struggle. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He displayed self-sacrificing spirit and bravery in many battles and died a heroic death in an unexpected engagement with Japanese imperialist troops in June 1935. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Indeed, his life was a brilliant life dedicated to the cause of the liberation and freedom of the nation and the revolutionary cause of the working-class.

Greetings to Russian PM and FM
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, June 12 (KCNA) -- Pak Pong Ju, premier of the DPRK Cabinet, sent a message of greetings to Mikhail Yefimovich Fradkov, prime minister of the Russian government, on the occasion of the national day of the Russian Federation.
 The message wished him and the government of the Russian Federation greater success in their work for the socio-economic progress of the country and the promotion of people's well-being, expressing the belief that the friendly and cooperative relations between the DPRK and Russia would grow stronger in various fields in the future. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Foreign Minister Paek Nam Sun sent a similar massage to his Russian counterpart Sergei Viktorovich Lavrov on the same occasion. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The message wished him greater success in his responsible work to protect the international prestige and interests of the country, expressing belief that the traditional friendly and cooperative relations between the DPRK and Russia favorably developing under the deep care of the top leaders of the two countries would more effectively grow stronger thanks to the close contacts and common efforts of the foreign policy executive organs of both sides.

Wreath Laid before Liberation Tower
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, June 12 (KCNA) -- The officials of the Russian embassy here placed a wreath before the Liberation Tower today on the occasion of the national day of Russia.
 Present at the wreath-laying ceremony were Ambassador Andrei Karlov and staff members of the Russian embassy and diplomatic envoys of various countries here. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Amid the playing of the wreath-laying music a wreath and bunches of flowers were placed before the Liberation Tower in the name of the Russian embassy. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Written on the ribbon of the wreath were letters "To fallen heroes".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The participants looked round the tower after paying silent tribute to the soldiers of the Soviet Army who fell in the battles for Korea's liberation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Then they laid a wreath and bunches of flowers before the cemetery of fallen fighters of the Soviet Army in Sadong District, Pyongyang.

Wreaths Laid before Bust of Kim Chol Ju
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, June 12 (KCNA) -- Wreaths were laid before the bust of indomitable revolutionary fighter Kim Chol Ju at the Revolutionary Martyrs Cemetery on Mt. Taesong on Monday on the occasion of his 90th birth anniversary.
 Seen before his bust was a wreath sent by Supreme Commander of the Korean People's Army Kim Jong Il, general secretary of the Workers' Party of Korea and chairman of the DPRK National Defence Commission. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present at the wreath-laying ceremony were Vice-President of the Presidium of the Supreme People's Assembly Yang Hyong Sop, secretaries of the WPK Central Committee Kim Ki Nam and Kim Jung Rin, officials of party and working people's organizations and ministries and working people in the city. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A wreath was laid before his bust in the name of the Central Committee of the WPK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 And then wreaths were laid in the name of working people's organizations, ministries and universities. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Written in the ribbons of wreaths were letters "In Memory of Revolutionary Fighter Comrade Kim Chol Ju".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The participants observed a moment's silence in memory of Kim Chol Ju.
